f the Venerable Seraphim of Sarov] Orthodox [[icon]] and [[synaxarion]]\n*[http://www.blagogon.ru/articles/89/ Glorification of Saint Seraphim. Sarov, 1903]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20120330183441/http://mmom.dev.armd.ru/ru/gallery/reports/index.php?id_7=79&from_7=19 Photos of St. Seraphim glorification solemnity in Sarov (1903)], Martha and Mary Convent site\n*[http://vesti.sarov.net/?id=22148 Photos of St. Seraphim glorification in Sarov (high res images)], sarov.net\n*[http://www.serfes.org/lives/stseraphin.htm St. Seraphim's biography] by Archimandrite Nektarios Serfes\n*[http://www.serafim100.ru/ Portal devoted to 100-th anniversary of St. Seraphim of Sarov glorification] (in Russian)\n*[http://www.sarov-monastery.org/english/ English page on Sarov monastery web-site]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n{{Catholic saints}}\n[[Category:Catholic saints|*]]\n[[Category:Lists of saints|Catholic]]\n\n[[Category:1759 births]]\n[[Category:1833 deaths]]\n[[Category:18th-century Christian saints]]\n[[Category:18th-century Christian mystics]]\n[[Category:19th-century Christian saints]]\n[[Category:19th-century Christian mystics]]\n[[Category:Ascetics]]\n[[Category:Eastern Orthodox mystics]]\n[[Category:Russian Eastern Orthodox priests]]\n[[Category:Russian saints of the Eastern Orthodox Church]]\n[[Category:Eastern Catholic saints]]\n[[Category:Catholic saints]]\n[[Category:Hesychasm]]\n[[Category:Starets]]\n[[Category:Wonderworkers]]\n[[Category:18th-century Eastern Orthodox priests]]\n[[Category:19th-century Eastern Orthodox priests]]\n", "name_user": "Chris the speller", "label": "safe", "comment": "typo", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Seraphim_of_Sarov"}
{"title_page": "Triumph (The Jacksons album)", "text_new": "{{Infobox album\n| name         = Triumph\n| type         = studio\n| artist       = [[The Jackson 5|the Jacksons]]\n| cover        = Jacksons-triumph.jpg\n| alt          = \n| released     = {{start date|1980|10|18}}<ref>https://www.thejacksons.com/history/the-jacksons-1980/</ref>\n| recorded     = 1980<ref name=\"Wax\">{{cite web|author=Chris Williams|url=https://www.waxpoetics.com/blog/features/articles/the-jacksons-triumph-engineer-tom-perry/|title=Engineer Tom Perry on the making of the Jacksons\u2019 1980 album Triumph|publisher=[[Wax Poetics]]|date=2016-06-23|accessdate=2019-11-10}}</ref>\n| studio       = [[Capitol Studios|Capitol Records Studios]]<br>Hollywood Sound<br>Davien Sound<br>[[Sound City Studios]]<br>[[Devonshire Sound Studios]]<br>[[Westlake Recording Studios|Westlake Audio]]<br>(Hollywood, California)\n| genre        = {{hlist|[[Post-disco]]|[[Rhythm and blues|R&B]]|[[funk]]|[[Soul music|soul]]}}\n| length       = 44:39\n| label        = [[Epic Records|Epic]]\n| producer     = The Jacksons\n| prev_title   = [[Boogie (album)|Boogie]]\n| prev_year    = 1979\n| next_title   = [[The Jacksons Live!]]\n| next_year    = 1981\n| misc         = {{Singles\n | name        = Triumph\n | type        = Studio\n | single1     = [[Lovely One]]\n | single1date = September 27, 1980\n | single2     = [[This Place Hotel]]\n | single2date = December 5, 1980\n | single3     = [[Can You Feel It (The Jacksons song)|Can You Feel It]]\n | single3date = March 5, 1981\n | single4     = [[Walk Right Now]]\n | single4date = June 15, 1981\n}}\n}}\n{{Album ratings\n| rev1 = [[AllMusic]]\n| rev1Score = {{Rating|4|5}}<ref>{{Allmusic|class=album|id=r41556/review|title=The Jacksons - ''Triumph'' (1980) album review by Andy Kellman, credits & releases}}</ref>\n| rev2 = [[Robert Christgau]]\n| rev2Score = A-<ref>[http://www.robertchristgau.com/get_album.php?id=3663 The Jacksons - ''Triumph'' (1980) album review by Robert Christgau]</ref>\n| rev3 = ''[[The Rolling Stone Album Guide]]''\n| rev3Score = {{Rating|4.5|5}}<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=t9eocwUfoSoC&pg=PA410&dq=rolling+stone+jackson+5+album+guide&hl=en&sa=X&ei=PM_5ULSXDafs0QGOroDwCg&ved=0CC0Q6AEwAA#v=onepage&q=rolling%20stone%20jackson%205%20album%20guide&f=false The New Rolling Stone Album Guide]</ref>\n}}\n\n'''''Triumph''''' is the fourteenth [[studio album]] by [[the Jacksons]], released in 1980 on [[Epic Records]].\n\nIt was certified platinum in the US and peaked at No. 10 on the [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]]. The ''Triumph'' album sold three million copies in its original run. Hit singles from the album were \"Lovely One\", \"Heartbreak Hotel\" (which was renamed \"[[This Place Hotel]]\" to avoid confusion with the [[Elvis Presley]] [[Heartbreak Hotel|song of the same name]]) and \"[[Can You Feel It (The Jacksons song)|Can You Feel It]]\".\n\nThe Jacksons shared [[Singing|lead vocals]] and solo spots on some songs, but [[Michael Jackson]], who had recently released his multi-platinum selling album, ''[[Off the Wall (album)|Off the Wall]]'', handles most of the lead vocal and writing duties. ''Triumph'' was the Jacksons' first album to reach number-one on the ''Billboard'' [[Billboard charts|R&B Albums chart]] since ''[[Maybe Tomorrow (The Jackson 5 album)|Maybe Tomorrow]]'' in 1971. The album sold over two million copies worldwide,<ref>Chery, Carl: ''XXL: Michael Jackson Special Collecters Edition'', page 100. American Press.</ref> and the Jacksons did not release another studio LP until ''[[Victory (The Jacksons album)|Victory]]'' in 1984. On December 10, 1980, the album was certified Platinum for the sales of over 1 million copies in the United States.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.riaa.com/goldandplatinumdata.php?table=SEARCH_RESULTS/ |title=Recording Industry Association of America |publisher=RIAA |accessdate=2012-03-12 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20120629082431/http://www.riaa.com/goldandplatinumdata.php?table=SEARCH_RESULTS/ |archivedate=2012-06-29 }}</ref>\n\n==Re-release==\n''Triumph'', with three bonus tracks of rare 7-inch and 12-inch mixes previously unavailable on CD, was re-released on January 27, 2009 on Epic/Legacy, a division of [[Sony Music Entertainment]].<ref>[http://www.legacyrecordings.com/News/NewsDetail.aspx?NewsGuid=aae9d0f4-0059-485b-8f27-bdac65e1e236 LegacyRecordings.com \u00bb News<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080709044158/http://www.legacyrecordings.com/News/NewsDetail.aspx?NewsGuid=aae9d0f4-0059-485b-8f27-bdac65e1e236 |date=2008-07-09 }}</ref>\n\n==Track listing==\n{{Track listing\n| title1  = [[Can You Feel It (The Jacksons song)|Can You Feel It]]\n| writer1 = [[Michael Jackson]]\n| length1 = 6:00\n| title2  = [[Lovely One]]\n| writer2 = Michael Jackson\n| length2 = 4:52\n| title3  = Your Ways\n| writer3 = Jackie Jackson\n| length3 = 4:31\n| title4  = Everybody\n| writer4 = Michael Jackson\n| length4 = 5:00\n| title5  = [[This Place Hotel]]\n| writer5 = Michael Jackson\n| length5 = 5:44\n| title6  = Time Waits for No One\n| writer6 = Jackie Jackson, Randy Jackson\n| length6 = 3:24\n| title7  = [[Walk Right Now]]\n| writer7 = Michael Jackson\n| length7 = 6:29\n| title8  = Give It Up\n| writer8 = Michael Jackson\n| length8 = 4:20\n| title9  = Wondering Who\n| writer9 = Jackie Jackson, Randy Jackson\n| length9 = 4:19\n}}\n\n{{Track listing\n| collapsed = no\n| headline = 2009 re-edition bonus tracks\n| title10  = This Place Hotel\n| note10   = Single Version\n| length10 = 4:52\n| title11  = Walk Right Now\n| note11   = John Luongo Disco Mix\n| length11 = 7:36\n| title12  = Walk Right Now\n| note12   = John Luongo Instrumental Mix\n| length12 = 6:58\n}}\n\n==Personnel==\n===The Jacksons===\n*[[Michael Jackson]] \u2013 Songwriter, Composer,lead and backing vocals, hand claps, hiccups\n*[[Jackie Jackson]] \u2013 backing vocals, lead vocals (track 9)\n*[[Tito Jackson]] \u2013 guitar, backing vocals\n*[[Marlon Jackson]] \u2013 backing vocals, timpani (track 5), co-lead vocals (track 8)\n*[[Randy Jackson (The Jacksons)|Randy Jackson]] \u2013 percussion, backing vocals, co-lead vocals (track 1)\n\n===Additional personnel===\n{{Div col}}\n*[[David Williams (guitarist)|David Williams]] \u2013 guitar (1-5, 7-9)\n*[[Paul Jackson, Jr.]] \u2013 guitar (5)\n*Greg Poree \u2013 guitar (6)\n*[[Michael Sembello]] \u2013 guitar (2, 5, 8)\n*[[Phil Upchurch]] \u2013 guitar (3)\n*[[Michael Boddicker]] \u2013 synthesizer (7, 9)\n*[[Ronnie Foster]] \u2013 keyboards (1, 9)\n*Webster Lewis \u2013 synthesizer (7)\n*[[Greg Phillinganes]] \u2013 keyboards (1-9), synthesizers (7)\n*Gary Coleman \u2013 vibraphone (1, 7, 8)\n*Clay Drayton \u2013 bass (6, 8)\n*Mike McKinney \u2013 bass (4)\n*[[Nathan Watts]] \u2013 bass (1-3, 5, 7)\n*[[Ollie E. Brown]] \u2013 drums (1, 2, 4-9)\n*Lenny Castro \u2013 percussion (9)\n*[[Paulinho da Costa]] \u2013 percussion (2, 3, 5-8)\n*Gary Herbig \u2013 flute (7)\n*Larry Hall \u2013 horns (4, 7)\n*[[Jerry Hey]] \u2013 horns (4, 5, 7)\n*Kim Hutchcroft \u2013 horns (4, 7)\n*[[Bill Reichenbach Jr.|Bill Reichenbach]] \u2013 horns (4, 7)\n*[[La Toya Jackson]] \u2013 voice scream (5)\n*Julia Tillman Waters, Maxine Willard Waters, Stephanie Spruill \u2013 backing vocals (track 5)\n*Audra Tillman, Brian Stilwell, Brigette Bush, Gerry Gruberth, Lita Aubrey, Peter Wade, Rhonda Gentry, Roger Kenerly II, Soloman Daniels, Yolanda Kenerly \u2013 backing vocals (The Children's Choir) (track 1)\n*Arnold McCuller, Bob Mack, Bunny Hull, Carmen Twillie, [[Carolyn Dennis]], Gerry Garrett, Gregory Wright, Jim Gilstrap, Josie James, Lewis Price, Lisa Roberts, Paulette Brown, Paulette McWilliams, Phyllis St. James, Tyrell \"Rock\" Deadrick, Roger Kenerly-Saint, Ronald Vann, Roy Galloway, [[Venetta Fields]] \u2013 backing vocals (The Adults' Choir) (track 1)\n{{Div col end}}\n\n===Production===\n*Produced, arranged, written and composed by [[The Jackson 5|the Jacksons]] except for \"Everybody\" (written by Michael Jackson, Tito Jackson and Mike McKinney)\n*[[Greg Phillinganes]] \u2013 associate producer\n*Tom Perry \u2013 engineer\n*Tom \"Tom Tom 84\" Washington \u2013 arrangements on \"[[Can You Feel It (The Jacksons song)|Can You Feel It]]\", \"[[Lovely One]]\", \"Your Ways\", \"Heartbreak Hotel\" \n*[[Jerry Hey]] \u2013 arrangements on \"Everybody\", \"Heartbreak Hotel\"\n*[[Jerry Peters]] \u2013 arrangements on \"Time Waits for No One\", \"Give It Up\", and string arrangements (6, 8)\n\n==Outtakes==\n*\"Slipped Away\" <small>(Michael Jackson, Marlon Jackson)</small>\n*\"That Girl\" <small>(Michael Jackson, Marlon Jackson, Randy Jackson, Jackie Jackson, Tito Jackson)</small>\n*\"Why Can't I Be\" <small>(Michael Jackson)</small>\n*\"Lovely Way\" \n\n== Charts ==\n\n=== Album ===\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n!scope=\"col\"|Chart (1980)\n!scope=\"col\"|Peak<br />position\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Australian Albums ([[Kent Music Report]]) <ref>{{cite book|title=Australian Chart Book 1970\u20131992|last=Kent|first=David|publisher=Australian Chart Book, St Ives, NSW|year=1993|isbn=0-646-11917-6|format=doc|title-link=Kent Music Report}}</ref>\n| 13\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Canadian Albums (''[[RPM (magazine)|RPM]]'') <ref name=\"Canadian album positions\">{{cite web |url = http://www.collectionscanada.gc.ca/rpm/028020-110.01-e.php?PHPSESSID=h6banu1fsvdt9pof8c4m7dun24&q1=village+people&q2=Top+Albums%2FCDs&interval=50 |title = RPM: The Jacksons (albums) |publisher = RPM Magazine |accessdate = April 12, 2017}}</ref>\n| 7\n|-\n{{album chart|Netherlands|25|artist=The Jacksons|album=Triumph|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 12, 2017}}\n|-\n{{album chart|New Zealand|8|artist=The Jacksons|album=Triumph|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 12, 2017}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Sweden|46|artist=The Jacksons|album=Triumph|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 12, 2017}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| UK Albums ([[Official Charts Company|OCC]]) <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/artist/16176/jacksons/|title=The Jacksons Chart History|publisher=Official Charts Company|accessdate=April 12, 2017}}</ref>\n| 13\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| US [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]]<ref name=\"VPb\">{{cite web |url=http://www.billboard.com/artist/416684/jacksons/chart?f=305|title=The Jacksons US Chart History |work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=April 12, 2017}}</ref>\n| 10\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| US [[Top R&B/Hip-Hop Albums|Hot Black Albums]]<ref>[https://www.billboard.com/music/the-jacksons/chart-history/r-b-hip-hop-albums The Jackson 5 / The Jacksons ''Billboard'' chart history]</ref>\n| 1 \n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Zimbabwean Albums ([[List of record charts|ZIMA]]) <ref>Zimbabwe. Kimberley, C. ''Zimbabwe: albums chart book''. Harare: C. Kimberley, 2000</ref>\n| 10\n|}\n\n===Singles===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\"| Year\n! rowspan=\"2\"| Single\n! colspan=\"3\"| Chart positions<ref name=\"allmusic singles\">{{cite web|url={{Allmusic|class=artist|id=p198366/charts-awards/billboard-singles|pure_url=yes}}|title=The Jacksons US singles chart history|publisher=AllMusic|accessdate=2011-08-05}}</ref>\n|- style=\"font-size:smaller;\"\n! style=\"width:40px;\"| [[Billboard Hot 100|US]]\n! style=\"width:40px;\"| [[Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Songs|US<br>R&B]]\n! style=\"width:40px;\"| [[Hot Dance Club Songs|US<br>Dance]]\n|-\n||1980\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| \"[[Lovely One]]\"\n| 12\n| 2\n| 1\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"|1981\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| \"[[Can You Feel It (The Jacksons song)|Can You Feel It]]\"\n| 77\n| 30\n| 1\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| \"[[This Place Hotel]]\"\n| 22\n| 2\n| &mdash;\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| \"[[Walk Right Now]]\"\n| 73\n| 50\n| 1\n|}\n\n==Certifications==\n{{Certification Table Top}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=New Zealand|type=album|title=Triumph|artist=The Jacksons|award=Gold|relyea